{
  format: 1
  name: generated-value-per-call-site-unspecified
  suite: scenario
  spec: ["#expressions", "§6.5", "§5.1", "§8.12"]
  tags: ["purity", "identity"]
  note: "Spec gap. §5.1: 'Generative values such as uuid() and now() are produced once for the admitted insertion'; §8.12: uuid() and now() 'produce their value once for an admitted request.' Read literally, one uuid value per request would make the two inserted rows collide on their uuid key defaults and reject the call; read as 'each evaluation site produces its value once (no re-evaluation on replay)', the rows get distinct ids and the call succeeds with count 2. Annex A.5 disambiguates now() (every call observes the same instant) but nothing disambiguates uuid(). The outcome diverges observably, so it is unspecified."

  package: {
    $liasse: 1
    $app: "t.uuidgen@1.0.0"
    $model: {
      rows: {
        $key: "id"
        id: "uuid = uuid()"
        name: "text"
      }
      $mut: {
        add_two: [
          ".rows + { name: 'x' }"
          ".rows + { name: 'y' }"
          "return count(.rows)"
        ]
      }
      $public: {
        rows: {
          $mut: { add_two: ".add_two" }
        }
      }
    }
  }

  steps: [
    { call: "public.rows.add_two", args: {},
      expect: { outcome: unspecified } }
  ]
}
